Relation to host — The mites cause tunnel galls on the leaf upper surface (
Fig. 3
). The galls are up to 3 mm long, trichomatose ("hairy") and have a middorsal longitudinal slit opening. They occur appressed to the leaf ribs or on the leaf blade. Up to 4 galls have been observed on one leaflet.
